[More and more countries are moving to apps that include tracking of current infections both to track if they are observing isolation or quarantine protocols, as well as to alert individuals if there have been active virus infected individuals near where they are. South Korea was one of the early users of such an app, Germany just launched an app on Wednesday, 17 Jun 2020. While there are individuals against the use of these apps for "privacy" reasons, they have had overall fairly widespread acceptance and use in countries where they have been implemented.

Screenshots of the app can be found at the source URL above. Searching for the meaning of Tarassud in Arabic, it means "observing steadily with attentive eyes, expecting, waiting, hoping. (in Urdu, Turkish, and Farsi it means waiting, hoping), and apt name for this app. (https://tinyurl.com/ybbn8lrr)

Maps of Oman can be seen at https://geology.com/world/oman-satellite-image.shtml and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7496025,124. Oman shares a border with Saudi Arabia, the United Arab Emirates, and Yemen - with Saudi Arabia and Yemen reporting high daily case counts. - Mod.MPP]

